Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App lost focus (e.g., notification shade pulled down)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- **OnPause** (Android) maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event — the app lost focus but may still be visible.
- **OnStop** (Android) and **DidEnterBackground** (iOS) both map to the cross-platform `Stopped` event — the UI is no longer visible.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback signatures, you can simply override `OnStopped()` on a `Window` subclass — MAUI will invoke it on both platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
protected override void OnStopped()
{
    base.OnStopped();
    Preferences.Set("draft", _vm.Draft);
}
```
